Casa Self-Hosting Roadmap
=========================

Goal: Eliminate the Python compiler entirely. Casa compiles itself,
tests itself, and provides its own language server — all in Casa.

Current state: The self-hosted compiler (self_hosted/) is feature-complete.
All 86 OpKinds, 69 InstKinds, 12 TokenKinds match the Python reference.
Bootstrap test proves Python → stage1 → stage2 → hello_world works.


Phase 1: Bootstrap Verification
--------------------------------
Prove the self-hosted compiler correctly compiles everything.

1.1  All-examples test
     Compile all 32 examples with stage2, run each binary, diff output
     against examples/outputs/*.out and multi_error.err.

1.2  Fixed-point bootstrap
     Python → stage1 → stage2 (keep .s) → stage3 (keep .s).
     Verify stage2.s and stage3.s are identical.
     Fix any divergences until the assembly output is a fixed point.

1.3  Bug fixes
     Fix any bugs surfaced during 1.1 and 1.2.


Phase 2: Test Migration
------------------------
Port critical Python tests to Casa so the self-hosted suite catches regressions.
16 Casa test files already exist. Focus on the largest gaps:

  File                      Python tests   Priority
  test_enum.py              186            HIGH
  test_typechecker.py       185            HIGH
  test_traits.py            73             HIGH
  test_struct_literal.py    34             MEDIUM
  test_type_annotations.py  36             MEDIUM
  test_generic_structs.py   19             MEDIUM

2.1  Identify missing coverage by diffing Python tests against Casa assertions.
2.2  Port HIGH priority tests (typechecker, enum, traits).
2.3  Port MEDIUM priority tests (struct_literal, type_annotations, generic_structs).
2.4  Update test runner to accept a compiler binary path argument.


Phase 3: Build System & CI
----------------------------
Infrastructure for building, testing, and distributing without Python.

3.1  Makefile
     Targets: bootstrap, stage1, stage2, verify, test, test-examples,
     install, clean. Support BOOTSTRAP=python for dev.

3.2  GitHub Release workflow
     Triggered on version tags. Build stage1 from Python, stage2 from
     stage1, verify fixed-point, publish casa-linux-x86_64 binary +
     SHA256 checksum.

3.3  Update CI workflows
     Download release binary → build stage2 → run all tests.
     Modify test scripts to accept compiler path argument.

3.4  Bootstrap documentation (BOOTSTRAP.md)
     How to build from release binary, from Python, fixed-point explanation.


Phase 4: LSP Rewrite in Casa
------------------------------
Replace casa_ls.py (1245 lines Python) with a Casa implementation.

4.0  Standard library prerequisites

     4.0.1  JSON parser/serializer (lib/json.casa, ~500 lines)
            JsonValue enum, json_parse, json_serialize.
            Handle string escapes, integers, arrays, objects, booleans, null.

     4.0.2  Buffered stdin reader (lib/io.casa, ~100 lines)
            stdin_read_byte, stdin_read_exact, stdin_read_line.

     4.0.3  String utilities (add to lib/std.casa, ~120 lines)
            str::split, str::trim, str::replace, str::contains.

4.1  JSON-RPC protocol layer (~250 lines)
     Read Content-Length header, read JSON body, parse, dispatch, respond.

4.2  LSP message types (~500 lines)
     Structs for Initialize, TextDocument, Diagnostic, Hover,
     CompletionItem, etc. Each with from_json/to_json methods.

4.3  Compilation pipeline for LSP (~250 lines)
     Resilient mode: collect errors without aborting.
     DocumentState cache per open file.

4.4  Diagnostics handler (~100 lines)
4.5  Go-to-definition handler (~175 lines)
4.6  Hover handler (~175 lines)
4.7  Completion handler (~250 lines)
4.8  Find references + rename handlers (~175 lines)
4.9  Semantic tokens handler (~225 lines)
4.10 Server main loop and initialization (~100 lines)

     Estimated total: 2000-3500 lines of Casa.

     Known risks:
     - Memory: Casa uses alloc (brk) with no freeing. Long-running LSP
       will grow. Accept initially; arena allocator can be added later.
     - Error recovery: may need resilient parsing mode in self-hosted parser.


Phase 5: Cleanup & Documentation
----------------------------------
Remove all Python from the repository.

5.1  Delete Python compiler: casa.py, casa/ directory.
5.2  Delete Python tests: tests/test_*.py, tests/conftest.py, casa_ls.py.
5.3  Update CI: remove setup-python, pip install. Replace test-unit.yml
     with self-hosted test workflow.
5.4  Update documentation: README.md (remove Python requirement, update
     install/usage), CLAUDE.md (remove Python conventions), docs/.
5.5  Final verification: fresh clone → download release binary →
     make stage2 → make test → make test-examples → LSP works in editor.


